You&#39;re filtering `vm.statuses`, and then saving the filtered result in `vm.statuses`. So, the next time you filter, you&#39;re filtering the previously filtered result. You should store the filtered results in a separate observable array so that the original, unfiltered array remains intact and can be filtered again. I see references to `vm.filteredStatuses` in your code, so maybe all you need to do is change:

    vm.statuses(filtered);

to:

    vm.filteredStatuses(filtered);

And obviously, show `filteredStatuses` in your UI instead of `statuses`.

